{
  "texts": [
    "This might be because we used MAE as the loss function.",
    "The MAE is a metric tailored toward the mean of a distribution, and therefore smaller values in the batch may be misrepresented without increasing the MAE.",
    "Moreover, the model is optimized by minimization of the MAE.",
    "Thus, it places more emphasis on suitably estimating large landslides and potentially underestimating the smaller ones.",
    "This problem could also have been influenced by the log-transformation step introduced at the beginning of the training process."
  ]
}